heroTitle.en-US: If you are struggling and need support, I can help. I offer psychotherapy for individuals, couples and families and look forward to connecting with you soon.

ctaTitle.en-US: Deciding to make that first contact with a therapist can be an intimidating and often overwhelming prospect.

ctaText.en-US: It's common to put therapy off due to fear, financial constraints, stigma, or other concerns. When you’re ready to reach out, I’ll do my best to help you feel as comfortable as possible so you can begin to move forward meaningfully in your life..

howCanIHelpTitle.en-US: Some of the many challenges I can support you through include:

cta2Text.en-US: My services are covered by most extended health benefit plans and some sliding scale options are available based on financial need. Please reach out to find out more.

introText.en-US:
Individual Therapy

I am invested in each individual's journey toward wholeness, offering the guidance and support needed to move in this direction.

Couple Therapy

Whether couples are just starting out on their journey together or are trying to find their way back to a happier time, I help them understand themselves and their relationship dynamics so they can create and sustain a new and healthy connection.

Family Therapy

From parenting to conflict, I do my best to help families leave behind the same old arguments and begin to find balance in the home.

Discernment Counselling

Some couples may be considering divorce but are not completely sure that’s the best path. Discernment Counseling is a new way of helping couples where one person is “leaning out” of the relationship—and not sure that regular marriage counseling would help--and the other is“leaning in”—that is, interested in rebuilding the marriage. 

I can help these couples decide whether to try to restore the marriage to health, move toward divorce, or take a time out and decide later. 

We work together to help each person gain clarity and confidence about a direction, based on a deeper understanding of their relationship and its possibilities for the future. 

Clinical Supervision

I offer clinical supervision for qualifying Registered Psychotherapists and Registered Marriage and Family Therapists who need to satisfy their clinical hours with CRPO and CAMFT, respectively. I am also available to meet with more seasoned psychotherapists looking to maintain or enhance their therapeutic skills. I am available to meet in a dyadic or group format, depending on the supervisee’s needs and preferences. 

Online Services

It’s not always easy to meet with me in person. Thankfully, video therapy overcomes barriers such as distance, scheduling, child-care, transportation, and illness because clients can meet with me securely wherever they are on their computer, tablet, or phone. Whether clients choose to meet exclusively by video or through a combination of in-person and video, we can find an arrangement that meets their need for flexibility.

whatToExpect.en-US: We’ll start with a brief phone conversation so that I can get a sense of the kind of support that you are looking for. I’ll ask for some basic information to get to know you and also use this time to answer any questions that you might have. If it feels like we are a good fit for working together, we will schedule an in-person appointment.

In the first few sessions, I will learn more about you and together, we will explore the goals you have for therapy. Do you want to build healthier relationships? Learn how to better manage emotions and stress? Or even identifying patterns that keep us feeling "stuck" in our lives.

introText.en-US:
Credentials

I am a Registered Psychotherapist with the College of Registered Psychotherapists of Ontario (CRPO), a Registered Marriage and Family Therapist with the American Association for Marriage and Family Therapy (AAMFT), and a Clinical Supervisor. I hold a Masters degree in Counselling from Tyndale University College and Seminary and an honours degree in Psychology from the University of Guelph. I value ongoing professional development and regularly attend training that enhances my therapeutic skills. 

Counselling Approach

I believe in a holistic approach to therapy that focuses on the emotional, physical, cognitive, relational, and spiritual well-being of my clients. My training in Family Systems Theory continually invites me to consider each person as part of a broader past and present social context. Building on this foundation, I integrate various theories and models into therapy, drawing primarily on Internal Family Systems Therapy, Emotion Focused Therapy, Focusing, and Mindfulness. Each of these models helps clients access their natural inner resources to find balance within themselves and their relationships.

Areas of Interest

Anxiety

I help clients understand and heal their relationship with anxiety, including phobias, perfectionism, social anxiety, and generalized anxiety

Trauma

Many clients have been through painful experiences that overwhelmed their capacity to cope. These experiences often continue to show up in ways that negatively affect their present life, such as anxiety, depression, addictions, and relationship struggles. I help clients build the skills they need to overcome the effects of trauma and begin to experience the inner calm they long for.

Relationships

Relationship Enrichment: For couples wanting to move toward more loving and satisfying relationships, I support them every step of the way

Relationship Discernment: I work with couples that are at a crossroads in their relationship to discern the future of their relationship and move toward a mutually satisfying outcome.

Infidelity: Whether infidelity is undisclosed, has just been uncovered, or continues to be a wedge in the relationship despite the passage of time, I work with couples to recover from its impact in a way that fits their unique circumstances.
